we'd have an opportunity

00:02:14.520 --> 00:02:16.980
to say, in person, thank
you to Kim Kardashian

00:02:16.980 --> 00:02:19.290
West for the fact
that she went to see

00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:20.850
the President of
the United States

00:02:20.850 --> 00:02:24.300
and asked him to look into
the situation of this woman,

00:02:24.300 --> 00:02:26.340
this amazing woman
you're going to meet,

00:02:26.340 --> 00:02:31.290
who ended up serving 21
years of a lifetime sentence

00:02:31.290 --> 00:02:37.100
in jail for a first-time,
non-felony drug offense.

00:02:37.100 --> 00:02:39.800
If she had committed that
crime today, few of us

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:41.660
doubt she would even
spent a day in jail.

00:02:41.660 --> 00:02:44.200
But retroactivity
isn't part of the game.

00:02:44.200 --> 00:02:45.620
So she kept herself together.

00:02:45.620 --> 00:02:47.690
She kept her spirits together.

00:02:47.690 --> 00:02:51.842
And again, her family kept that
hope alive so that she knew,

00:02:51.842 --> 00:02:54.050
when she was coming home,
she was coming home to such

00:02:54.050 --> 00:02:56.090
a loving and supportive family.

00:02:56.090 --> 00:02:58.100
And what so many people
who are dealing in this

00:02:58.100 --> 00:03:00.650
have told me is the difference
between those who make it

00:03:00.650 --> 00:03:02.900
and those who don't are
the support structure

00:03:02.900 --> 00:03:03.680
outside the jail.

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:05.630
So again, thank you
for keeping our star

00:03:05.630 --> 00:03:07.430
together so that
she can continue

00:03:07.430 --> 00:03:09.447
to shine a light on all of us.

00:03:09.447 --> 00:03:11.030
So I've been asked,
just very briefly,

00:03:11.030 --> 00:03:14.071
to set the stage for why Google
is involved in criminal justice

00:03:14.071 --> 00:03:14.570
reform.

00:03:14.570 --> 00:03:17.030
So working out of
Washington, DC, Malika and I

00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:19.370
have recognized that
it is really one

00:03:19.370 --> 00:03:21.170
of the few bipartisan issues--

00:03:21.170 --> 00:03:24.380
House, Senate,
Republicans, Democrats,

00:03:24.380 --> 00:03:26.420
governors throughout
the state, local leaders

00:03:26.420 --> 00:03:28.760
who understand that
the Criminal Justice

00:03:28.760 --> 00:03:30.800
Project that we have
in the United States--

00:03:30.800 --> 00:03:33.680
our system is anything
but just and that it needs

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:36.260
a lot of-- as David Drummond
once said, if there's anything

00:03:36.260 --> 00:03:38.750
that needs disrupting,
and we're disruptors, it's

00:03:38.750 --> 00:03:40.580
the criminal justice system.

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:43.010
It is a system that works
for very few people.

00:03:43.010 --> 00:03:46.280
And certainly, based on your
socioeconomics, your color,

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:49.590
and your gender, it's not
going to work for you at all.

00:03:49.590 --> 00:03:52.070
And so what we started to do
was look into ways that we,

00:03:52.070 --> 00:03:54.060
as Google, could help this.

00:03:54.060 --> 00:03:55.010
So we walked the walk.

00:03:55.010 --> 00:03:57.770
I think many of you know
Google bans the box where

00:03:57.770 --> 00:04:01.310
we don't ask people if they've
served any jail on their job

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:02.330
applications.

00:04:02.330 --> 00:04:09.770
We have banned bail bonds ads,
which keep many people together

00:04:09.770 --> 00:04:13.010
and owe exorbitant
prices by promises.

00:04:13.010 --> 00:04:15.530
And we didn't want to make money
off that in any way, shape,

00:04:15.530 --> 00:04:17.600
or form at Google.

00:04:17.600 --> 00:04:21.610
And then we decided that it
was time to do something more,

00:04:21.610 --> 00:04:24.330
to take our products
to tell a story,

00:04:24.330 --> 00:04:27.530
because we're convinced that
the people in this country

00:04:27.530 --> 00:04:30.680
are good people and that, if
they knew the truth about what

00:04:30.680 --> 00:04:33.410
goes on in our criminal
justice system,

00:04:33.410 --> 00:04:35.570
they would be enraged
and demand change.

00:04:35.570 --> 00:04:37.580
If they knew for a
fact that there's

00:04:37.580 --> 00:04:39.890
over 30 states that
still allow women

00:04:39.890 --> 00:04:42.440
to be shackled when
they're giving birth,

00:04:42.440 --> 00:04:44.120
they would be angry.

00:04:44.120 --> 00:04:46.340
If they knew that there are
women in this country who

00:04:46.340 --> 00:04:48.423
have to deal with whether
they should make a phone

00:04:48.423 --> 00:04:50.990
call to their family
or buy sanitary napkins

00:04:50.990 --> 00:04:53.690
or tampons because they are
considered, by our prison

00:04:53.690 --> 00:04:57.290
system, as non-essential,
every woman in this country

00:04:57.290 --> 00:04:59.030
would be very mad.

00:04:59.030 --> 00:05:01.040
If they knew that
the people at Rikers,

00:05:01.040 --> 00:05:03.620
one of the worst
places in this country,

00:05:03.620 --> 00:05:07.580
are consistent of 80% of
individuals who have not

00:05:07.580 --> 00:05:12.170
seen trial yet, innocent until
proven guilty, but spending

00:05:12.170 --> 00:05:16.100
years of their lives behind
bars because the only thing

00:05:16.100 --> 00:05:18.320
they can be convicted
of at that point

00:05:18.320 --> 00:05:21.680
is not having enough
money to make bail or get

00:05:21.680 --> 00:05:23.580
a good lawyer--

00:05:23.580 --> 00:05:28.910
so what we decided at Google
was the problem is nobody hears

00:05:28.910 --> 00:05:31.830
them, nobody sees them, right?

00:05:31.830 --> 00:05:35.580
We want to turn a blind eye
to all those injustices.

00:05:35.580 --> 00:05:38.150
But we have the products at
Google, particularly YouTube,

00:05:38.150 --> 00:05:40.340
that allows us to
crawl behind the wall

00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:43.520
and get behind the prison gates
so that we can tell their story

00:05:43.520 --> 00:05:45.060
and give them voice.

00:05:45.060 --> 00:05:48.260
And that's what we did here and
what we're continuing to do.

00:05:48.260 --> 00:05:51.080
So just very briefly, and
then I'm off the stage,

00:05:51.080 --> 00:05:54.280
we went with YouTube, and
with the help of Andy,

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:57.080
to put together a video
where Ms. Alice spoke

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:59.960
behind bars and behind
glass on a phone

00:05:59.960 --> 00:06:03.420
and talked about what 21
years away from her family,

00:06:03.420 --> 00:06:06.260
her children, her grandchildren,
now her great-grandchildren,

00:06:06.260 --> 00:06:09.980
have been for an offense
that she wished she never

00:06:09.980 --> 00:06:13.801
made, but just wants to get out
of prison to be with her family

00:06:13.801 --> 00:06:14.300
again.

00:06:14.300 --> 00:06:16.070
She talked about all
the other inmates

00:06:16.070 --> 00:06:19.070
that are in there in
the very same situation.

00:06:19.070 --> 00:06:21.860
And then there was a group
called [INAUDIBLE] she

00:06:21.860 --> 00:06:24.960
challenged everybody who
watched to go out there and tell

00:06:24.960 --> 00:06:27.140
these stories to give
faces to the faceless,

00:06:27.140 --> 00:06:30.110
to give voices to those people
who feel like no one else

00:06:30.110 --> 00:06:31.190
cares.

00:06:31.190 --> 00:06:34.280
And there was a
creator called mic.com,

00:06:34.280 --> 00:06:38.210
who wrote an op-ed on behalf of
Ms. Alice with our Google team.

00:06:38.210 --> 00:06:40.077
And that's what
Kim Kardashian saw

00:06:40.077 --> 00:06:42.410
and what she took to the
President of the United States.

00:06:42.410 --> 00:06:44.630
So Google, you helped do this.

00:06:44.630 --> 00:06:47.510
You helped to free this woman
so that she can bear witness

00:06:47.510 --> 00:06:49.010
to the stories that
need to be told.

00:06:49.010 --> 00:06:50.840
So congratulations,
Google, first of all.

00:06:50.840 --> 00:06:53.572
Yes, give everybody a
round of applause here.

00:06:53.572 --> 00:06:57.460
[APPLAUSE]

00:06:57.460 --> 00:07:01.630
In closing, just let me
say, today we celebrate,

00:07:01.630 --> 00:07:03.340
but we acknowledge our work.

00:07:03.340 --> 00:07:04.600
There's so much more to do.

00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:07.690
There's so many more souls
who are waiting to be rescued.

00:07:07.690 --> 00:07:10.690
And we know that when
we celebrate Ms. Johnson

00:07:10.690 --> 00:07:13.240
and thank these advocacy
organizations, who are also

00:07:13.240 --> 00:07:17.350
here, to whom we honor with
their presence, who have stood

00:07:17.350 --> 00:07:19.630
fast behind individuals
like Ms. Alice

00:07:19.630 --> 00:07:22.540
before Google ever got there
and kept their spirits up,

00:07:22.540 --> 00:07:24.310
we're honored to be
here with all of you.

00:07:24.310 --> 00:07:25.570
Thank you.

00:07:25.570 --> 00:07:28.430
So clearly, there are
still too many women, men,

00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:31.570
and children who are
made to feel powerless,

00:07:31.570 --> 00:07:34.510
and then whose families are
scarred and scared, and then

00:07:34.510 --> 00:07:37.780
whose neighborhoods are broken,
and then whose country is not

00:07:37.780 --> 00:07:40.390
living up to its full destiny.

00:07:40.390 --> 00:07:42.820
So with that, I want to
thank you all for being here

00:07:42.820 --> 00:07:44.840
to allow us to tell this story.

00:07:44.840 --> 00:07:47.130
And now I want to introduce
one of our partners, Andy

00:07:47.130 --> 00:07:48.700
[? Berndt ?] who,
most of you know,

00:07:48.700 --> 00:07:53.470
is from BrandLab, who has
sort of taken this up.

00:07:53.470 --> 00:07:55.960
He has been to, I think, four
or five prisons already--

00:07:55.960 --> 00:07:58.690
is going to San
Quentin next week--

00:07:58.690 --> 00:08:01.360
has used his genius to help
tell this story and help

00:08:01.360 --> 00:08:03.520
put together a lot
of what reached

00:08:03.520 --> 00:08:07.540
the imagination of individuals
throughout this country

00:08:07.540 --> 00:08:10.930
to help tell Ms. Alice's story
and so many others behind bars.

00:08:10.930 --> 00:08:13.570
He has really been
instrumental at Google

00:08:13.570 --> 00:08:15.360
in leading our
commitment to justice.

00:08:15.360 --> 00:08:16.632
Andy?

00:08:16.632 --> 00:08:19.894
[APPLAUSE]

00:08:20.594 --> 00:08:21.760
[? ANDY BERNDT: ?] Good job.

00:08:21.760 --> 00:08:22.290
Good job.

00:08:22.290 --> 00:08:23.590
SUSAN MOLINARI: I give big hug.

00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:25.710
[? ANDY BERNDT: ?]
How about that?

00:08:25.710 --> 00:08:27.820
OK, still not Kim Kardashian.

00:08:27.820 --> 00:08:29.885
[LAUGHTER]

00:08:29.885 --> 00:08:31.390
Just to be clear.

00:08:31.390 --> 00:08:34.539
So I'm only up here for
a few minutes, I promise.

00:08:34.539 --> 00:08:38.080
What I wanted to
say, though, was

00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:42.640
I would say about three years
ago, during a lot of the really

00:08:42.640 --> 00:08:44.260
tough Black Lives
Matter moments,

00:08:44.260 --> 00:08:46.895
we got together as
a team in New York.

00:08:46.895 --> 00:08:49.020
And a lot of Googlers, a
lot of people on the team,

00:08:49.020 --> 00:08:51.574
were feeling really
horrible, deeply horrible.

00:08:51.574 --> 00:08:52.990
And through a lot
of conversations

00:08:52.990 --> 00:08:54.150
what we realized was--

00:08:54.150 --> 00:08:55.840
and maybe we knew
this a little bit,

00:08:55.840 --> 00:08:57.280
but we didn't know it enough--

00:08:57.280 --> 00:08:59.620
that we really didn't
have enough understanding

00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:02.680
and empathy about the
way lots of people live.

00:09:02.680 --> 00:09:04.666
And Google, at its best--

00:09:04.666 --> 00:09:06.040
my favorite thing
about Google is

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:07.720
if you look around
hard enough, you

00:09:07.720 --> 00:09:10.634
will find a genius in any field.

00:09:10.634 --> 00:09:12.050
And they work
somewhere at Google.

00:09:12.050 --> 00:09:13.780
And you have to get
[INAUDIBLE] troll

00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:15.980
and all those sorts of things.

00:09:15.980 --> 00:09:17.630
But you will find them.

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:20.770
And we were lucky enough that,
with the help of a few friends,

00:09:20.770 --> 00:09:24.284
we we had families of
incarcerated people come in.

00:09:24.284 --> 00:09:26.200
We had previously
incarcerated people come in.

00:09:26.200 --> 00:09:28.575
We had all kinds of people
come in and just talk with us.

00:09:28.575 --> 00:09:31.540
So we knew a lot of people
by first name from a world

00:09:31.540 --> 00:09:34.240
that a lot of us didn't
really understand.

00:09:34.240 --> 00:09:36.700
I was going explain how then
Malika came to the scene.

00:09:36.700 --> 00:09:38.464
And I just asked
her, how did we meet?

00:09:38.464 --> 00:09:40.630
And she said, well, you
were looking for a bathroom.

00:09:40.630 --> 00:09:43.240
And you came in this conference
room, and you were like, what?

00:09:43.240 --> 00:09:44.156
And that's how we met.

00:09:44.156 --> 00:09:48.490
So that's not really
that great a story.

00:09:48.490 --> 00:09:52.030
However, I must
say about Malika--

00:09:52.030 --> 00:09:53.780
I think we've gone
to four prisons now--

00:09:53.780 --> 00:09:56.050
Detroit, women's
prison in New Jersey.

00:09:56.050 --> 00:09:57.640
We're going to San
Quentin next week.

00:10:01.090 --> 00:10:02.770
Malika's a special person.

00:10:02.770 --> 00:10:05.510
She is the kind of person that
you feel so lucky to know,

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:08.264
to meet, to have known,
to have worked with.

00:10:08.264 --> 00:10:09.680
She will take you
under her spell,

00:10:09.680 --> 00:10:11.221
and you will find
that you do things,

00:10:11.221 --> 00:10:13.010
whether you want to
or not, because she's

00:10:13.010 --> 00:10:15.140
told you to do them.

00:10:15.140 --> 00:10:16.760
And she's amazing.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:19.280
It makes me proud to work here
because I get to finally work

00:10:19.280 --> 00:10:20.422
with people like Malika.

00:10:20.422 --> 00:10:21.880
She's probably
embarrassed at this.

00:10:21.880 --> 00:10:25.460
But tough, she deserves it.

00:10:25.460 --> 00:10:27.710
My ability to get
my group involved

00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:30.920
in things that are meaningful
to them, that are important,

00:10:30.920 --> 00:10:34.340
that they feel are worth
everything they put into them,

00:10:34.340 --> 00:10:38.390
even if they're a
2%, 3%, 5% effort,

00:10:38.390 --> 00:10:40.400
makes all the difference.

00:10:40.400 --> 00:10:42.380
And it's all informal.

00:10:42.380 --> 00:10:44.091
It's all people
just meeting people.

00:10:44.091 --> 00:10:45.590
If you want to get
involved, I think

00:10:45.590 --> 00:10:47.090
Maab will talk about
how to do that.

00:10:47.090 --> 00:10:48.950
But if you have
the ability to get

00:10:48.950 --> 00:10:52.857
involved in any kind of
these efforts, just do.

00:10:52.857 --> 00:10:53.760
Just get it started.

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:57.590
All it needs is a few friends
and someone who cares.

00:10:57.590 --> 00:10:59.000
And people will back you up.

00:10:59.000 --> 00:11:01.180
So I'm supposed to
also introduce a video

00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:02.700
and mostly get off the stage.

00:11:02.700 --> 00:11:04.520
You'll see a video
here that's kind of

00:11:04.520 --> 00:11:08.070
made by a whole lot of
people, pieces from all over.

00:11:08.070 --> 00:11:10.190
It's nice that it was
one of the things that

00:11:10.190 --> 00:11:12.590
kicked this whole
thing into motion,

00:11:12.590 --> 00:11:15.560
