work for you in trying

00:31:46.410 --> 00:31:49.230
to fight mass
incarceration, in trying

00:31:49.230 --> 00:31:54.360
to talk about the ways in which
our families, our communities,

00:31:54.360 --> 00:31:59.580
have been broken because of the
very real costs of this type

00:31:59.580 --> 00:32:03.080
of over-criminalization?

00:32:03.080 --> 00:32:04.610
ALICE JOHNSON: The main thing--

00:32:04.610 --> 00:32:06.140
I believe the main
purpose that I'm

00:32:06.140 --> 00:32:09.230
serving in lifting up
my voice and showing you

00:32:09.230 --> 00:32:12.560
my face is to
humanize this issue.

00:32:12.560 --> 00:32:16.430
Someone has to humanize
this issue so that you just

00:32:16.430 --> 00:32:19.670
don't read about
a person, you just

00:32:19.670 --> 00:32:22.420
don't see some
numbers or a profile

00:32:22.420 --> 00:32:27.920
that someone has fed you about
a person, that you see me.

00:32:27.920 --> 00:32:29.600
You see my family.

00:32:29.600 --> 00:32:31.400
You see my friends.

00:32:31.400 --> 00:32:33.470
You see others when you see me.

00:32:33.470 --> 00:32:36.620
And I must continue to
fight for this issue

00:32:36.620 --> 00:32:42.200
because, as I asked Google, and
you came up to the challenge,

00:32:42.200 --> 00:32:45.120
if not you, then who?

00:32:45.120 --> 00:32:46.997
If not me, then who?

00:32:46.997 --> 00:32:48.330
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: That's right.

00:32:48.330 --> 00:32:49.220
That's right.

00:32:49.220 --> 00:32:54.500
