00:35:03.610 --> 00:35:06.700
And I don't care who it
was who brought me out,

00:35:06.700 --> 00:35:07.930
who signed my papers.

00:35:07.930 --> 00:35:09.160
I don't care.

00:35:09.160 --> 00:35:12.130
I'm so thankful to be
sitting here looking out

00:35:12.130 --> 00:35:14.710
at this audience today.

00:35:14.710 --> 00:35:18.460
And I hope that others will get
the courage to do something,

00:35:18.460 --> 00:35:21.340
to act, and to
take this cause up,

00:35:21.340 --> 00:35:25.420
because people very lives
are dependent upon them

00:35:25.420 --> 00:35:27.410
and are dependent upon you.

00:35:27.410 --> 00:35:28.660
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: Absolutely.

00:35:28.660 --> 00:35:30.874
And it's not just about
the White House, right?

00:35:30.874 --> 00:35:32.040
ALICE JOHNSON: No, it's not.

00:35:32.040 --> 00:35:35.290
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: It
really is about how

00:35:35.290 --> 00:35:37.654
part of the war on
drugs was dehumanizing.

00:35:37.654 --> 00:35:38.570
ALICE JOHNSON: It was.

