And it seems like
so much of the work

00:35:57.340 --> 00:35:59.424
is also about changing
popular culture.

00:35:59.424 --> 00:36:00.340
ALICE JOHNSON: It has.

00:36:00.340 --> 00:36:03.180
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: Reframing
what the war on drugs

00:36:03.180 --> 00:36:03.995
really was about.

00:36:03.995 --> 00:36:05.120
ALICE JOHNSON: That's true.

00:36:05.120 --> 00:36:09.610
I believe that there should
be punishment for crime.

00:36:09.610 --> 00:36:11.290
There should be punishment.

00:36:11.290 --> 00:36:15.250
And as I've said this before,
people are quick to say,

00:36:15.250 --> 00:36:16.840
you do the crime,
you do the time.

00:36:16.840 --> 00:36:18.040
Don't cry now.

00:36:18.040 --> 00:36:20.470
But that time should
also be fair and just,

00:36:20.470 --> 00:36:23.909
based on the crime, not unjust.

00:36:23.909 --> 00:36:27.262
[APPLAUSE]

00:36:27.262 --> 00:36:31.560
So I don't believe that
the communities were

00:36:31.560 --> 00:36:35.910
safer because I spent
almost 22 years of my life

00:36:35.910 --> 00:36:39.360
behind bars-- a first-time,
non-violent offender,

00:36:39.360 --> 00:36:44.130
no criminal history, no
convictions, no trials, nothing

00:36:44.130 --> 00:36:48.330
of any kind, was a
productive member of society

00:36:48.330 --> 00:36:51.270
until that one mistake.

00:36:51.270 --> 00:36:55.110
A bad call on my part,
but it should not

00:36:55.110 --> 00:36:56.650
have cost me my life.

00:36:56.650 --> 00:36:59.610
And if it had not been
for someone having

00:36:59.610 --> 00:37:02.340
the courage, who's sitting
on my right hand right now,

00:37:02.340 --> 00:37:05.340
Kim Kardashian, to
take up my cause

00:37:05.340 --> 00:37:06.630
and go to the White House--

00:37:06.630 --> 00:37:09.490
