Well, I want to
end with gratitude.

00:45:07.280 --> 00:45:10.840
I'm so grateful to
you for showing us

00:45:10.840 --> 00:45:13.810
the best of who we
are, as a company

00:45:13.810 --> 00:45:18.070
I'm so grateful for how
you have been through hell

00:45:18.070 --> 00:45:23.560
and back and always insisted
on dignity and grace.

00:45:23.560 --> 00:45:25.935
I am grateful to you
for that example.

00:45:25.935 --> 00:45:27.310
ALICE JOHNSON:
Thank you, Malika.

00:45:27.310 --> 00:45:29.351
MALIKA SAADA SAAR: And I
am grateful to you, Kim,

00:45:29.351 --> 00:45:33.520
for your courage
to be an activist,

00:45:33.520 --> 00:45:38.500
to be able to be a voice
against the over-criminalization

00:45:38.500 --> 00:45:41.150
of our families and
our communities.

00:45:41.150 --> 00:45:42.120
Thank you.

00:45:42.120 --> 00:45:47.080
It is an example that you set
that we all have to adhere to

00:45:47.080 --> 00:45:49.030
and recognize.

00:45:49.030 --> 00:45:51.250
And I also want to
express gratitude

00:45:51.250 --> 00:45:55.150
not only to this remarkable
community of Googlers

00:45:55.150 --> 00:45:59.560
